Name: mammary Paget's disease
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that has_material_basis_in epidermal Paget cells

Name: breast signet ring cell adenocarcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by the presence of numerous cells containing intracellular mucin
Synonym: signet ring cell carcinoma of breast

Name: breast mucinous carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma in which at least one half of the tumor volume is extracellular mucin throughout.

Name: breast secretory carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that has_material_basis_in cells with abundant granular or clear vacuolated cytoplasm.

Name: glycogen-rich clear cell breast carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by predominantly clear cytoplasm due to glycogen.

Name: obsolete miscellaneous mesenchymal neoplasm
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by predominantly clear cytoplasm due to glycogen.

Name: breast medullary carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by a syncitial growth pattern and high grade cytology.

Name: acinic cell breast carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by widespread acinar cell-like differentiation.

Name: inflammatory breast carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by the clinical appearance of inflammation

Name: obsolete recurrent extraskeletal chondrosarcoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by the clinical appearance of inflammation

Name: breast apocrine carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm

Name: oncocytic breast carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized by abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm due to large numbers of mitochondria.

Name: invasive tubular breast carcinoma
Definition: A breast adenocarcinoma that is characterized as a well-differentiated invasive carcinoma with regular cells arranged in well-defined tubules (typically one layer thick) surrounded by an abundant fibrohyaline stroma.
